- "Prolific" refers to the artists with the highest number of tracks in the top three genres.;
- "Top three genres" are the genres with the most tracks.;
- "Acousticness" is a measure of how acoustic a track sounds.;
- "Danceability" is a measure of how suitable a track is for dancing.

- 'Sunflowers blooming brightly' refers to artists with an average popularity score greater than 50;
- 'More than 10 songs' refers to artists with more than 10 tracks;
- 'Most vibrant and flourishing genre' refers to the genre with the highest number of tracks.

- "top 10 tracks" refers to the tracks with the highest number of recommendations;
- "stars in the musical sky" is a metaphor for highly recommended tracks;
- "well-defined palette of preferences" indicates that users have specified preferences for genre, mood, and artist.

- "Discovered" refers to the user having listened to the track at least once;
- "Love" refers to the user's preferred artists and genres based on their preferences;
- "Acclaimed" refers to the track's popularity score being higher than the average of the user's most listened tracks.
